  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html lang=\"en\">\n<head>\n  <meta charset=\"utf-8\" />\n  <title>Two Pointers — Interactive Demo</title>\n  <meta name=\"viewport\" content=\"width=device-width,initial-scale=1\" />\n  <style>\n    :root{\n      --bg:#0f1724;\n      --card:#0b1220;\n      --muted:#94a3b8;\n      --accent:#38bdf8;\n      --good:#22c55e;\n      --bad:#fb7185;\n      --glass: rgba(255,255,255,0.03);\n    }\n    html,body{height:100%; margin:0; font-family:Inter,ui-sans-serif,system-ui,Segoe UI,Roboto,\"Helvetica Neue\",Arial; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#071029 0%, #071426 60%); color:#e6eef8;}\n    .wrap{max-width:1100px;margin:28px auto;padding:20px;}\n    header{display:flex; gap:20px; align-items:center; margin-bottom:18px;}\n    header h1{font-size:20px;margin:0;color:var(--accent);}\n    .card{background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.02), rgba(255,255,255,0.01)); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03); padding:16px; border-radius:10px;}\n    .controls{display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; margin-top:12px; flex-wrap:wrap;}\n    select,input[type=\"text\"],input[type=\"number\"]{background:var(--glass); color:var(--muted); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03); padding:8px 10px; border-radius:8px; min-width:160px;}\n    button{background:transparent; color:var(--accent); border:1px solid rgba(56,189,248,0.12); padding:8px 12px; border-radius:8px; cursor:pointer;}\n    button.secondary{background:transparent; color:var(--muted); border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03);}\n    .play{background:linear-gradient(90deg,#06b6d4,#3b82f6); color:#012; border:none;}\n    .top-row{display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between;}\n    .left-pane, .right-pane{padding:12px; border-radius:10px;}\n    .grid{display:grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 420px; gap:18px;}\n    .visual{min-height:220px; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(255,255,255,0.01), rgba(255,255,255,0.00)); border-radius:10px; padding:18px; }\n    .array-row{display:flex; gap:10px; align-items:flex-end; justify-content:center; flex-wrap:wrap;}\n    .cell{width:52px; height:52px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.02); border-radius:8px; border:1px solid rgba(255,255,255,0.03); display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:center; position:relative; color:var(--muted); font-weight:600;}\n    .cell.active{background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(56,189,248,0.09), rgba(56,189,248,0.02)); color:var(--accent); box-shadow:0 6px 20px rgba(56,189,248,0.06);}\n    .cell.good{background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(34,197,94,0.09), rgba(34,197,94,0.02)); color:var(--good);}\n    .cell.bad{background:linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(251,113,133,0.08), rgba(251,113,133,0.02)); color:var(--bad);}\n    .pointer{position:absolute; top:-28px; left:50%; transform:translateX(-50%); font-size:12px; color:var(--muted);}\n    .pointer.arrow::after{content:\"▼\"; display:block; margin-top:2px; color:var(--muted);}\n    .bar{width:44px; background:linear-gradient(180deg,#60a5fa,#0369a1); border-radius:6px; display:flex; align-items:flex-end; justify-content:center; color:#012; font-weight:700; margin:0 6px;}\n    .bars{display:flex; gap:6px; align-items:flex-end; height:140px; padding:12px;}\n    .code{background:#07101a; padding:12px; border-radius:8px; color:#cfefff; font-family:ui-monospace,SFMono-Regular,Menlo,Monaco,monospace; font-size:13px; overflow:auto; max-height:180px;}\n    .meta{display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; margin-top:12px; color:var(--muted); font-size:13px;}\n    .footer{margin-top:14px; color:var(--muted); font-size:13px;}\n    .controls .small{font-size:13px; padding:6px 8px;}\n    .speed{width:140px;}\n    .stepper{display:flex; gap:8px; align-items:center;}\n    .status{font-size:14px; color:var(--muted);}\n    label{font-size:13px; color:var(--muted)}\n    .explain{margin-top:12px; color:var(--muted); line-height:1.5; font-size:14px;}\n    @media (max-width:900px){ .grid{grid-template-columns:1fr; } .right-pane{order:2;} }\n  </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n  <div class=\"wrap\">\n    <header>\n      <div>\n        <h1>Two Pointers — Interactive Demo</h1>\n        <div class=\"meta\">Explore classic two-pointer patterns with step-by-step visualization. Pick a problem, set inputs, and step through the algorithm.</div>\n      </div>\n      <div style=\"margin-left:auto; text-align:right;\">\n        <div style=\"color:var(--muted); font-size:13px;\">Concepts: opposite-moving pointers, slow-fast, partitioning, in-place</div>\n      </div>\n    </header>\n\n    <div class=\"card grid\">\n      <div class=\"left-pane card\">\n        <div style=\"display:flex; gap:12px; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between;\">\n          <div style=\"min-width:0;\">\n            <label>Choose problem</label><br>\n            <select id=\"problemSelect\">\n              <option value=\"twoSum\">Two Sum (sorted array) — find pair with target</option>\n              <option value=\"removeDup\">Remove Duplicates (in-place) — unique count</option>\n              <option value=\"partitionParity\">Partition by Parity — even left, odd right</option>\n              <option value=\"containerWater\">Container With Most Water — max area</option>\n            </select>\n          </div>\n\n          <div style=\"min-width:0;\">\n            <label>Input array (comma separated)</label><br>\n            <input id=\"arrayInput\" type=\"text\" value=\"1,2,3,4,6,8\" />\n          </div>\n\n          <div id=\"targetBox\" style=\"min-width:0;\">\n            <label>Target (for Two Sum)</label><br>\n            <input id=\"targetInput\" type=\"number\" value=\"10\" />\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"controls\" style=\"margin-top:14px;\">\n          <button id=\"resetBtn\" class=\"secondary small\">Reset & Generate Steps</button>\n          <button id=\"prevBtn\" class=\"small\">Prev</button>\n          <button id=\"playBtn\" class=\"small play\">Play</button>\n          <button id=\"nextBtn\" class=\"small\">Next</button>\n\n          <div class=\"stepper\" style=\"margin-left:auto;\">\n            <label>Speed</label>\n            <input id=\"speed\" type=\"range\" min=\"200\" max=\"2000\" value=\"900\" class=\"speed\" />\n            <div class=\"status\" id=\"stepStatus\">Step 0 / 0</div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"visual\" style=\"margin-top:14px;\">\n          <div id=\"visualArea\" style=\"width:100%;\"></div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"explain\" id=\"explainBox\">\n          Select a problem and generate steps. Use Play to animate the two-pointer movement.\n        </div>\n\n      </div>\n\n      <div class=\"right-pane card\">\n        <div>\n          <label>Algorithm (pseudocode)</label>\n          <pre class=\"code\" id=\"codeBox\"></pre>\n        </div>\n\n        <div style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n          <label>Current state details</label>\n          <div class=\"card\" style=\"margin-top:8px; padding:12px; background:rgba(255,255,255,0.01);\">\n            <div id=\"stateDetails\" style=\"color:var(--muted); font-size:13px;\">No steps yet.</div>\n            <div style=\"margin-top:8px; color:var(--muted); font-size:13px;\" id=\"resultBox\"></div>\n          </div>\n        </div>\n\n        <div class=\"footer\" style=\"margin-top:12px;\">\n          Time: O(n) or O(n log n) depending on sort. Space: O(1) extra for in-place.\n        </div>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </div>\n\n<script>\n(() => {\n  // Helper functions\n  function $id(id){return document.getElementById(id);}\n  function parseArray(s){\n    if(!s) return [];\n    return s.split(',')\n      .map(t=>t.trim())\n      .filter(t=>t.length>0)\n      .map(t=>{\n        // allow numbers\n        let n = Number(t);\n        return isNaN(n) ? t : n;\n      });\n  }\n\n  // Elements\n  const problemSelect = $id('problemSelect');\n  const arrayInput = $id('arrayInput');\n  const targetInput = $id('targetInput');\n  const targetBox = $id('targetBox');\n  const resetBtn = $id('resetBtn');\n  const prevBtn = $id('prevBtn');\n  const nextBtn = $id('nextBtn');\n  const playBtn = $id('playBtn');\n  const visualArea = $id('visualArea');\n  const codeBox = $id('codeBox');\n  const explainBox = $id('explainBox');\n  const stateDetails = $id('stateDetails');\n  const resultBox = $id('resultBox');\n  const stepStatus = $id('stepStatus');\n  const speedRange = $id('speed');\n\n  // State\n  let steps = [];\n  let stepIndex = 0;\n  let playing = false;\n  let timer = null;\n\n  // Problem definitions\n  function twoSumSteps(arr, target){\n    // expects sorted array of numbers\n    let a = arr.slice();\n    let left = 0, right = a.length - 1;\n    const out = [];\n    out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'start', compare:null}));\n    while(left < right){\n      let sum = a[left] + a[right];\n      out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'compare', compare:sum}));\n      if(sum === target){\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'found', result:[left,right]}));\n        return out;\n      } else if(sum < target){\n        left++;\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'move_left'}));\n      } else {\n        right--;\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'move_right'}));\n      }\n    }\n    out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'not_found'}));\n    return out;\n  }\n\n  function removeDuplicatesSteps(arr){\n    // In-place unique count for sorted array\n    let a = arr.slice();\n    let n = a.length;\n    if(n === 0) return [snapshot(a,0,-1,{msg:'empty'})];\n    let write = 1;\n    let i = 1;\n    const out = [];\n    out.push(snapshot(a, 0, 1, {msg:'start', write}));\n    while(i < n){\n      out.push(snapshot(a, i, write, {msg:'compare', compare:[a[i], a[write-1]]}));\n      if(a[i] !== a[write-1]){\n        // copy\n        a[write] = a[i];\n        out.push(snapshot(a, i, write, {msg:'copy', write}));\n        write++;\n      } else {\n        out.push(snapshot(a, i, write, {msg:'skip_equal'}));\n      }\n      i++;\n    }\n    out.push(snapshot(a, i-1, write-1, {msg:'done', result:write}));\n    return out;\n  }\n\n  function partitionParitySteps(arr){\n    // partition evens to left, odds to right in-place\n    let a = arr.slice();\n    let left = 0, right = a.length - 1;\n    const out = [];\n    out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'start'}));\n    while(left < right){\n      // advance left until odd\n      while(left < right && a[left] % 2 === 0){\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'skip_even_left'}));\n        left++;\n      }\n      // advance right until even\n      while(left < right && a[right] % 2 !== 0){\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'skip_odd_right'}));\n        right--;\n      }\n      if(left < right){\n        // swap\n        [a[left], a[right]] = [a[right], a[left]];\n        out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'swap', swap:[left,right]}));\n        left++; right--;\n      }\n    }\n    out.push(snapshot(a, left, right, {msg:'done'}));\n    return out;\n  }\n\n  function containerMostWaterSteps(arr){\n    // heights, compute max area\n    let height = arr.slice();\n    let left = 0, right = height.length - 1;\n    let maxArea = 0, best = [0,0];\n    const out = [];\n    out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'start', maxArea}));\n    while(left < right){\n      let h = Math.min(height[left], height[right]);\n      let area = h * (right - left);\n      out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'compare', compare:area, curr:[left,right], maxArea}));\n      if(area > maxArea){\n        maxArea = area;\n        best = [left, right];\n        out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'update_max', maxArea, best}));\n      }\n      // move smaller pointer\n      if(height[left] < height[right]){\n        left++;\n        out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'move_left'}));\n      } else {\n        right--;\n        out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'move_right'}));\n      }\n    }\n    out.push(snapshot(height, left, right, {msg:'done', maxArea, best}));\n    return out;\n  }\n\n  // Snapshot structure: {arr, left, right, meta}\n  function snapshot(arr, left, right, meta){\n    return {\n      arr: arr.slice(),\n      left: left,\n      right: right,\n      meta: meta || {}\n    };\n  }\n\n  // UI rendering\n  function renderStep(i){\n    if(!steps || steps.length === 0) {\n      visualArea.innerHTML = '<div style=\"color:var(--muted)\">No steps to display.</div>';\n      codeBox.textContent = '';\n      explainBox.textContent = 'Generate steps to see the visualization.';\n      stateDetails.textContent = '';\n      resultBox.textContent = '';\n      stepStatus.textContent = 'Step 0 / 0';\n      return;\n    }\n    stepIndex = Math.max(0, Math.min(i, steps.length-1));\n    const s = steps[stepIndex];\n    stepStatus.textContent = `Step ${stepIndex+1} / ${steps.length}`;\n    // Visual depends on problem\n    const problem = problemSelect.value;\n    if(problem === 'containerWater'){\n      renderBars(s);\n    } else {\n      renderArrayRow(s);\n    }\n    // Code & explanation\n    codeBox.textContent = codes[problem];\n    explainBox.innerHTML = explains[problem];\n    // State details\n    let d = '';\n    d += `left: ${s.left}  right: ${s.right}\\n`;\n    if(s.meta.compare !== undefined) d += `compare: ${JSON.stringify(s.meta.compare)}\\n`;\n    if(s.meta.write !== undefined) d += `write index: ${s.meta.write}\\n`;\n    if(s.meta.maxArea !== undefined) d += `current maxArea: ${s.meta.maxArea}\\n`;\n    if(s.meta.best) d += `best pair: ${JSON.stringify(s.meta.best)}\\n`;\n    d += `array: [${s.arr.join(', ')}]`;\n    stateDetails.textContent = d;\n    resultBox.textContent = renderResultText(s);\n  }\n\n  function renderResultText(s){\n    const meta = s.meta || {};\n    switch(meta.msg){\n      case 'found': return `Found target at indices ${meta.result[0]} and ${meta.result[1]}.`;\n      case 'not_found': return 'No pair sums to target.';\n      case 'done':\n        // might be different meanings\n        if(meta.result !== undefined) return `Unique count: ${meta.result}`;\n        if(meta.maxArea !== undefined) return `Max area: ${meta.maxArea} (between ${meta.best})`;\n        return 'Done.';\n      case 'update_max': return `New max area: ${meta.maxArea} between ${meta.best}`;\n      default: return '';\n    }\n  }\n\n  function renderArrayRow(s){\n    const arr = s.arr;\n    const left = s.left;\n    const right = s.right;\n    // build cells\n    const container = document.createElement('div');\n    container.className = 'array-row';\n    for(let idx=0; idx<arr.length; idx++){\n      const cell = document.createElement('div');\n      cell.className = 'cell';\n      if(idx === left || idx === right) cell.classList.add('active');\n      // coloring for found/skip/copy\n      if(s.meta.msg === 'found' && s.meta.result && (idx===s.meta.result[0] || idx===s.meta.result[1])) cell.classList.add('good');\n      if(s.meta.msg === 'copy' && idx === s.meta.write) cell.classList.add('good');\n      if(s.meta.msg === 'skip_equal' && idx === left) cell.classList.add('bad');\n      cell.textContent = arr[idx];\n      // pointer labels\n      if(idx === left || idx === right){\n        const p = document.createElement('div');\n        p.className = 'pointer arrow';\n        p.title = idx===left ? 'left' : 'right';\n        p.textContent = idx===left ? 'L' : 'R';\n        cell.appendChild(p);\n      }\n      container.appendChild(cell);\n    }\n    visualArea.innerHTML = '';\n    visualArea.appendChild(container);\n  }\n\n  function renderBars(s){\n    const arr = s.arr;\n    const left = s.left;\n    const right = s.right;\n    const maxVal = Math.max(1, ...arr.map(v => typeof v==='number'?v:1));\n    const bars = document.createElement('div');\n    bars.className = 'bars';\n    for(let i=0;i<arr.length;i++){\n      const val = Number(arr[i]) || 0;\n      const h = Math.max(4, Math.round((val / maxVal) * 120));\n      const bar = document.createElement('div');\n      bar.className = 'bar';\n      bar.style.height = `${h}px`;\n      bar.style.opacity = (i===left || i===right) ? '1' : '0.7';\n      if(i===left) bar.style.boxShadow = '0 6px 18px rgba(56,189,248,0.08)';\n      if(i===right) bar.style.boxShadow = '0 6px 18px rgba(251,113,133,0.06)';\n      bar.textContent = val;\n      // pointer labels\n      const lab = document.createElement('div');\n      lab.style.position='absolute';\n      bar.style.position='relative';\n      const p = document.createElement('div');\n      p.className = 'pointer arrow';\n      p.textContent = i===left ? 'L' : (i===right ? 'R' : '');\n      if(i===left || i===right) bar.appendChild(p);\n      bars.appendChild(bar);\n    }\n    visualArea.innerHTML = '';\n    visualArea.appendChild(bars);\n  }\n\n  // Step control\n  function play(){\n    if(playing) return;\n    playing = true;\n    playBtn.textContent = 'Pause';\n    playBtn.classList.remove('play');\n    advance();\n  }\n  function pause(){\n    playing = false;\n    playBtn.textContent = 'Play';\n    playBtn.classList.add('play');\n    if(timer) { clearTimeout(timer); timer=null; }\n  }\n  function advance(){\n    if(!playing) return;\n    if(stepIndex < steps.length - 1){\n      stepIndex++;\n      renderStep(stepIndex);\n      timer = setTimeout(advance, Number(speedRange.value));\n    } else {\n      pause();\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Generate steps based on selection\n  function generateSteps(){\n    pause();\n    const arr = parseArray(arrayInput.value);\n    let problem = problemSelect.value;\n    // Validate/prepare inputs\n    if(arr.length === 0){\n      alert('Please enter a non-empty array (comma separated).');\n      return;\n    }\n    // For two-sum and remove duplicates, algorithms assume sorted arrays.\n    // We'll automatically sort numbers when appropriate (inform the user).\n    // For partition & container, preserve order.\n    let gen = null;\n    if(problem === 'twoSum'){\n      // ensure numeric and sorted\n      const nums = arr.map(x=>Number(x));\n      if(nums.some(x=>isNaN(x))){\n        alert('Two Sum expects a numeric sorted array. Provide numbers.');\n        return;\n      }\n      nums.sort((a,b)=>a-b);\n      steps = twoSumSteps(nums, Number(targetInput.value));\n    } else if(problem === 'removeDup'){\n      const nums = arr.map(x=>Number(x));\n      if(nums.some(x=>isNaN(x))){\n        alert('Remove Duplicates expects numbers (sorted).');\n        return;\n      }\n      nums.sort((a,b)=>a-b);\n      steps = removeDuplicatesSteps(nums);\n    } else if(problem === 'partitionParity'){\n      // numeric array\n      const nums = arr.map(x=>Number(x));\n      if(nums.some(x=>isNaN(x))){\n        alert('Partition by parity expects numeric array.');\n        return;\n      }\n      steps = partitionParitySteps(nums);\n    } else if(problem === 'containerWater'){\n      const nums = arr.map(x=>Number(x));\n      if(nums.some(x=>isNaN(x))){\n        alert('Container With Most Water expects numeric array (heights).');\n        return;\n      }\n      steps = containerMostWaterSteps(nums);\n    } else {\n      steps = [];\n    }\n    stepIndex = 0;\n    renderStep(0);\n  }\n\n  // Event wiring\n  resetBtn.addEventListener('click', generateSteps);\n  prevBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { pause(); if(steps.length) renderStep(stepIndex-1); });\n  nextBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { pause(); if(steps.length) renderStep(stepIndex+1); });\n  playBtn.addEventListener('click', () => { if(playing) pause(); else play(); });\n\n  problemSelect.addEventListener('change', () => {\n    const p = problemSelect.value;\n    // show/hide target input\n    targetBox.style.display = (p === 'twoSum') ? 'block' : 'none';\n    // load example arrays for convenience\n    if(p === 'twoSum'){ arrayInput.value = '1,2,3,4,6,8'; targetInput.value='10'; }\n    if(p === 'removeDup'){ arrayInput.value = '0,0,1,1,1,2,2,3,3,4'; }\n    if(p === 'partitionParity'){ arrayInput.value = '3,2,1,4,6,5,7,8'; }\n    if(p === 'containerWater'){ arrayInput.value = '1,8,6,2,5,4,8,3,7'; }\n  });\n\n  // initial text for code and explanation\n  const codes = {\n    twoSum:\n`left = 0\nright = n - 1\nwhile left < right:\n  sum = a[left] + a[right]\n  if sum == target:\n    return [left, right]\n  if sum < target:\n    left += 1\n  else:\n    right -= 1`,\n    removeDup:\n`// for sorted array\nif n == 0: return 0\nwrite = 1\nfor i in 1..n-1:\n  if a[i] != a[write-1]:\n    a[write] = a[i]\n    write += 1\nreturn write // number of unique elements`,\n    partitionParity:\n`left = 0\nright = n - 1\nwhile left < right:\n  while left < right and a[left] is even: left += 1\n  while left < right and a[right] is odd: right -= 1\n  if left < right:\n    swap a[left], a[right]\n    left += 1; right -= 1`,\n    containerWater:\n`left = 0\nright = n - 1\nmaxArea = 0\nwhile left < right:\n  area = min(h[left], h[right]) * (right - left)\n  maxArea = max(maxArea, area)\n  if h[left] < h[right]:\n    left += 1\n  else:\n    right -= 1\nreturn maxArea`\n  };\n\n  const explains = {\n    twoSum:\n`Two pointers technique on sorted arrays: place one pointer at the start (L) and one at the end (R).\nCompute the sum a[L] + a[R]. If it equals the target we've found a pair.\nIf the sum is too small move L right to increase it; if too big move R left to decrease it.\nTime: O(n), Space: O(1).`,\n    removeDup:\n`In a sorted array, duplicates are adjacent. Use a \"write\" pointer that tracks where to place the next unique value.\nScan with i; when a[i] differs from the last written value, copy it to a[write] and increment write.\nThis yields the new length (write), and the first write elements are unique. In-place, O(1) extra space.`,\n    partitionParity:\n`Partition the array so that evens are on the left and odds on the right.\nUse two pointers from both ends: move left forward while it's even, move right backward while it's odd.\nWhen left finds an odd and right finds an even, swap them. Continue until pointers cross.`,\n    containerWater:\n`Given heights along the x-axis, two pointers at ends compute area formed by the shorter height times distance.\nAt each step, move the pointer at the shorter height inward—this might find a taller boundary and larger area.\nThis is O(n) time and O(1) space.`\n  };\n\n  // initialize\n  problemSelect.dispatchEvent(new Event('change'));\n  generateSteps();\n\n  // keyboard shortcuts\n  document.addEventListener('keydown', (e)=>{\n    if(e.key === ' ') { e.preventDefault(); if(playing) pause(); else play(); }\n    if(e.key === 'ArrowRight') { e.preventDefault(); pause(); renderStep(stepIndex+1); }\n    if(e.key === 'ArrowLeft') { e.preventDefault(); pause(); renderStep(stepIndex-1); }\n  });\n})();\n</script>\n</body>\n</html>"
  },
